            <text>
                <body>
                    <div type="edition">
                        <div type="textpart">
                            <ab><persName><name ref="Gregorius">Gregorii</name></persName> filio
                        quondam <persName><name ref="Maurizo">Maurici</name></persName> pro remedium
                        anime mee in proprio territurio meo <rs key="#Private_foundations">a
                            fundamentis fabricis <rs key="#Churches">ecclesiam</rs> construere visus
                            sum</rs> in honore et vocabulo <orgName
                            key="#Churches #Monasteries #Private_foundations"
                            ref="#juridical_persons/601">Sancti Donati</orgName> in <placeName
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie #Casalini/fundamenta #Petiae #Cereals #Wine #Fruits/vegetables #Churches #Monasteries #Private_foundations"
                            ref="#places/64">loco qui dicitur Asulari</placeName>. <foreign>Perciò
                            dona alla chiesa sé stesso</foreign> una cum omnibus rebus meis, tam <rs
                            key="#Casae/cassinae_massaricie">casa habitationis</rs> meae cum <rs
                            key="#Casalini/fundamenta">fundamento</rs>, curte, <rs
                            key="#Fruits/vegetables">orto</rs>, vel alia tecta vel fabrica, simul et
                            <rs key="#Cereals">terris</rs>, <rs key="#Wine">vineis</rs>, mobile vel
                        inmobile seu semoventibus (…); excepto duas <rs key="#Petiae">petiole</rs>
                        de terra mea: una petia qui est prope <rs key="#Petiae">terra</rs>
                        <persName key="#Confinia #Petiae"><name ref="Bonusolus"
                            >Bonusuli</name></persName> germani mei, alio vero <rs key="#Petiae"
                            >petiolo</rs> qui est <rs key="#Wine">vitis</rs> posita in loco qui
                        vocitatur <placeName key="#Petiae #Wine" ref="#places/486"
                            >Lamari</placeName>; iste predicte petiole in mea reservo potestate.
                            <foreign>Si riserva l’usufrutto dei beni e la nomina del rettore della
                            chiesa per la durata della vita.</foreign> Et pro anima mea de ipso
                        usufructu vel res mobile potestatem habeam elimosinam faciendum recto
                        moderamine. <foreign>Il prete nominato gli succeda come rettore se gli
                            sopravvivesse</foreign>. Sic tamen absque ulla femina ividem habitare
                        debeat et per singola ebdomada quattuor peregrini omni tempore die uno
                        pascere debeat. Post vero eius decessu volo atque instituo, ut prefata
                        ecclesia cum res ividem pertentente sit in potestate <rs
                            key="#Mother_churches">ecclesie</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/68">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName>, ubi est domo episcoporum vel <rs key="#Bishops"
                            >pontifici</rs> qui ividem fuerit ordinatus, ordinando et defendendo
                        sicut Deo placitum est (…) non ut ividem femina quilibet habitare debeat; et
                        qui presbiter ividem fuerit ordinatus (…) per singula septimana die uno
                        quattuor peregrini ividem pascere deveat. Et hoc volo, ut <persName
                            key="#Slave #Freedman"><name ref="Agulus">Aculo</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Slave">puero</rs>, <rs key="#Freedman">qui a me liver et absolutus
                            a servitio factus est</rs>, si caste tonso capite Deo servire voluerit,
                        habeat licentia introidendum in ipso <rs key="#Monasteries">monasterio</rs>
                        et lavorare et servire ividem sub potestate de <rs key="#Priests"
                            >presbitero</rs> qui ividem fuerit ordinatus. (…) Et presens pagina
                        dotalium et alia similis iste emissa in <rs key="#Mother_churches"
                            >ecelsia</rs>
                        <orgName key="#Mother_churches" ref="#juridical_persons/68">Sancti
                            Martini</orgName>
                        <persName key="#Writer #Deacons"><name ref="Osprandus"
                            >Osprandum</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Deacons">diaconum</rs> scrivere rogavi. Actum <placeName
                            ref="#places/4">Luca</placeName>. <foreign>Sottoscrizioni</foreign>: +
                        Gregori; + <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Gaifredus de Asulari"
                                >Gaifred</name></persName> de <placeName ref="#places/64"
                            >Asulari</placeName> testis; + <persName key="#Witness"><name
                                ref="Antenor">Anteneri</name></persName> filio quondam
                                <persName><name ref="Godiscalcus">Gudiscalc</name></persName>
                        testis; + <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Servulus"
                            >Serbuli</name></persName> de <placeName>Asulari</placeName> testis; +
                            <persName key="#Witness"><name ref="Maurizo de Asulari"
                            >Maurici</name></persName> de <placeName>Asulari</placeName> testis; +
                            <persName key="#Witness #Other_clerics"><name ref="Rotchis"
                                >Rotchis</name></persName>
                        <rs key="#Other_clerics">clerici</rs> filio Solduli <rs key="#Other_clerics"
                            >clerici</rs> testis. <foreign>Scrive</foreign>: Osprandus
                        diaconus.</ab>
